[Experimental] The ActionSearch API returns all actions (relations) that a subject can perform on a specific resource. This is useful for answering questions like "What can Anne do with this document?" or building dynamic UIs that show only the actions a user is permitted to perform.

## Examples
### Find all actions a user can perform on a document
```json
{
  "subject": {"type": "user", "id": "anne"},
  "resource": {"type": "document", "id": "roadmap"}
}
